:: StoryTitle
IGC Library


:: StoryData
{
  "ifid": "D9B2C4A1-3F8E-4B72-A1C5-8E2D9F0B4C3A",
  "format": "SugarCube",
  "format-version": "1.0.35",
  "start": "StartPage",
  "zoom": 1
}


:: Bookshelf {"position":"800,325","size":"100,100"}
<<if not $hasBookshelfKey>>
The bookshelf is behind a sheet of glass. The glass door has a small keyhole in the frame.

//You'll need a key to open this.//

[[← Go back->Room]]
<<else>>
You unlock the glass door with the key, giving you access to the books inside.

Six shelves (left to right): ''General Works, Philosophy & Psychology, Natural Science, Technology, Art, Language.''

Books to sort:

<<if not $shelf1>>
A yellow-spined book appears: //"Put me in the correct shelf."//
Where does it go?

* [[General Works->ShelfBook1GW]] | [[Philosophy & Psych->ShelfBook1PP]] | [[Natural Science->ShelfBook1NS]] | [[Technology->ShelfBook1Tech]] | [[Art->ShelfBook1Art]] | [[Language->ShelfBook1Lang]]
<<elseif not $shelf2>>
A white book: //"James Bond with code name ###"//
Where does it go?

* [[General Works->ShelfBook2GW]] | [[Philosophy & Psych->ShelfBook2PP]] | [[Natural Science->ShelfBook2NS]] | [[Technology->ShelfBook2Tech]] | [[Art->ShelfBook2Art]] | [[Language->ShelfBook2Lang]]
<<elseif not $shelf3>>
A blue and yellow book: //"Which language do you speak?"//
Where does it go?

* [[General Works->ShelfBook3GW]] | [[Philosophy & Psych->ShelfBook3PP]] | [[Natural Science->ShelfBook3NS]] | [[Technology->ShelfBook3Tech]] | [[Art->ShelfBook3Art]] | [[Language->ShelfBook3Lang]]
<<else>>
All books correctly shelved! The shelves tremble and something falls to the floor —

''Your student ID card!'' It must have been hidden between the books.

<<set $hasStudentId to true>>

✦ //You acquired the Student ID!//

[[← Go back->Room]]
<</if>>
<</if>>


:: Computer {"position":"800,200","size":"100,100"}
<<if not $computerUnlocked>>
A small laptop on the study room's desk. The screen shows it's locked — profile: ''User005.133''. There's a password field below.

Hint left by the user: //"Just try to simplify. Simple like a cup of coffee."//

The Dewey Decimal system… perhaps the password relates to a book's call number.

Password: <<textbox "$password" "" autofocus>>

<<button "Unlock">>
  <<if $password is "M849s" or $password is "M849S">>
    <<set $computerUnlocked to true>>
    <<goto "Computer">>
  <<else>>
    Incorrect. Remember: //"Just try to simplify. Simple like a cup of coffee."//
  <</if>>
<</button>>
<<else>>
The computer is open. There's an email application and a sparse desktop.

[[Open the email->Email]] | [[Close the computer->Room]]
<</if>>

[[← Go back->Room]]


:: Door {"position":"550,200","size":"100,100"}
The door is sturdy and wooden with no visible handle. It appears to slide in and out on an unseen track. Next to it is a small card reader where a student ID could be swiped.

<<if $hasStudentId>>
You have your student ID. 

[[Swipe the card->Escape]] | [[← Go back->Room]]
<<else>>
//You don't have a card you could use here.//

[[← Go back->Room]]
<</if>>


:: Email {"position":"925,200","size":"100,100"}
There is only one conversation in the inbox — an exchange between three users.

<div style="background:#e8ddc8;border:1px solid #d4c9b0;border-radius:4px;padding:1.25rem;margin:0.75rem 0;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.9;">
''Robert:'' Where is the third librarian
''Martin:'' What?
''Robert:'' The little figurine.
''Cecil:'' Which one?
''Robert:'' God, do you people not listen? The third one. Librarian C.
''Martin:'' Ohhhh
''Cecil:'' I thought you had it, Robby?
''Robert:'' Obviously not. That's why I'm asking you guys.
''Martin:'' I left it in the box for safe keeping.
''Robert:'' And what was the code?
''Martin:'' Something thematic. One that all three of us could figure out together.
''Cecil:'' huh?
''Martin:'' Think about it. Try to put our heads together and think it through.
''Robert:'' I get it.
''Cecil:'' HUH????
''Martin:'' Try to find the three of us on the bookshelf, genius.
</div>

The conversation ends there. The word box... and three names hidden somewhere.

[[← Go back->Computer]]


:: Escape {"position":"900,600","size":"100,100"}
<div class="ending">

As you swipe the card you hear an affirmative beep.
The door slides away automatically, revealing a deep darkness beyond.

<glow>You're free.</glow>

As you step through the threshold, the nightmare you've been trapped in each night fades away.

<strong>''You wake up.''</strong>

</div>
<div class="ending-menu">
[[Return to SOMNI LIBRARY->StartPage]]
</div>


:: FigA {"position":"1300,200","size":"100,100"}
You press the button on Librarian A's head. With a soft click, the head swings off on its hinge, revealing a small cavity inside.

Inside is a tiny brass key. A tag reads: ''«Bookshelf Key»''

<<set $hasBookshelfKey to true>>

✦ //You acquired the Bookshelf Key!//

[[← Back to figurines->Librarians]]


:: FigB {"position":"1425,200","size":"100,100"}
You press the button on Librarian B's head. Nothing happens. The figurine stares back at you impassively.

//Perhaps this isn't the truth-teller…//

[[← Back to figurines->Librarians]]


:: FigC {"position":"300,325","size":"100,100"}
You press the button on Librarian C's head. Nothing happens. The figurine stares back at you impassively.

//Perhaps this isn't the truth-teller…//

[[← Back to figurines->Librarians]]


:: FigD {"position":"425,325","size":"100,100"}
You press the button on Librarian D's head. Nothing happens. The figurine stares back at you impassively.

//Perhaps this isn't the truth-teller…//

[[← Back to figurines->Librarians]]


:: Librarians {"position":"1175,200","size":"100,100"}
<<if not $wordBoxSolved or not $hasLibrarianC>>
The figurines sit on the floor — ''A'', ''B'', and ''D''. Figurine ''C'' is conspicuously absent.

//With Library Figurine C absent, you can't fully solve this puzzle yet. The word box in the corner might reveal where Librarian C has been hidden...//

[[Go to the word box →->WordBox]] | [[← Go back->Room]]
<<else>>
All four figurines are present on the floor — ''A'', ''B'', ''C'', and ''D''.

Written on the floor beneath them: //"The librarians of Computer Science. At least one of them is lying. Choose one of them that is telling the truth."//

Each has a button on the back of its head.

* [[Librarian A — "There is exactly 1 truth-teller among us. The printing room has 6 computers."->FigA]]
* [[Librarian B — "There are exactly 2 truth-tellers among us. The printing room has less than 6 computers."->FigB]]
* [[Librarian C — "There are exactly 2 liars among us. The printing room has 5 computers."->FigC]]
* [[Librarian D — "There are exactly 8 computers in the printing room."->FigD]]

[[← Go back->Room]]
<</if>>


:: Room {"position":"425,200","size":"100,100"}
The study room stretches around you. The smell of dust is overwhelming.

Behind you is an exit door. In front of you are wall-to-wall bookcases with blank books. On a desk sits a small computer. In one corner is a safe; in the opposite corner, a wooden box like an armoire. Four librarian figurines huddle together on the floor — or should be four.

What do you examine?

* [[The exit door->Door]]
* [[The bookshelf->Bookshelf]]
* [[The computer->Computer]]
* [[The librarian figurines->Librarians]]
* [[The word box->WordBox]]


